# ALSHAM 360° PRIMA - Cursor Rules

You are working on ALSHAM 360° PRIMA, an enterprise CRM with 150+ modules, cyberpunk design, and 6 dynamic themes.

## CRITICAL RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)

### 1. ZERO HARDCODED COLORS
NEVER use:
- `bg-white`, `bg-black`, `bg-gray-*`
- `text-white`, `text-gray-*`, `text-emerald-*`, `text-blue-*`
- `border-gray-*`, `border-blue-*`
- Hex colors like `#fff`, `#10b981`

ALWAYS use CSS variables:
- `bg-[var(--surface)]` instead of `bg-white`
- `bg-[var(--bg)]` instead of `bg-gray-900`
- `text-[var(--text)]` instead of `text-white`
- `text-[var(--text-secondary)]` instead of `text-gray-500`
- `border-[var(--border)]` instead of `border-gray-200`

### 2. USE SHADCN/UI COMPONENTS
Always import from `@/components/ui/`:
```tsx
import { Card, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input'
import { Table, TableBody, TableCell, TableHead, TableHeader, TableRow } from '@/components/ui/table'
```

### 3. REAL DATA ONLY
- NO mock data, fake data, or placeholders
- Always use Supabase queries
- Always filter by `org_id` for multi-tenancy

### 4. PRESERVE FUNCTIONALITY
- Keep framer-motion animations
- Keep Supabase realtime subscriptions
- Keep Recharts/Chart.js integrations
- Never remove existing features

## COLOR MAPPING

```
bg-white → bg-[var(--surface)]
bg-gray-50/100 → bg-[var(--surface-strong)]
bg-gray-800/900 → bg-[var(--bg)]
text-white → text-[var(--text)]
text-gray-500 → text-[var(--text-secondary)]
text-gray-900 → text-[var(--text-primary)]
border-gray-* → border-[var(--border)]

# Status colors
green → bg-[var(--accent-emerald)]/10 text-[var(--accent-emerald)]
blue → bg-[var(--accent-sky)]/10 text-[var(--accent-sky)]
yellow → bg-[var(--accent-warning)]/10 text-[var(--accent-warning)]
red → bg-[var(--accent-alert)]/10 text-[var(--accent-alert)]
purple → bg-[var(--accent-purple)]/10 text-[var(--accent-purple)]
```

## VALIDATION BEFORE COMMIT

```bash
# Check for hardcoded colors (must return empty)
grep -rn "bg-gray-\|bg-white\|text-gray-[0-9]" src/pages/

# Check for shadcn/ui imports (must be > 0)
grep -c "@/components/ui" src/pages/[FILE].tsx

# Build test
npm run build
```

